---
import ToolLayout from '../../../layouts/ToolLayout.astro';
import {
  buildSoftwareApplicationSchema,
  buildFAQSchema,
  buildWebPageWithSpeakable,
} from '../../../lib/schema-builders';

const pageTitle = 'Free Internal Link Suggester — Find Link Opportunities Instantly | theStacc';
const pageDescription = 'Analyze any webpage and discover internal linking opportunities. Get specific anchor text suggestions, target page recommendations, and priority rankings. Free, no signup required.';
const pageUrl = 'https://thestacc.com/tools/internal-link-suggester/';
const lastUpdated = '2026-05-11';

const softwareSchema = buildSoftwareApplicationSchema({
  name: 'Free Internal Link Suggester',
  description: 'Analyze webpage content and discover internal linking opportunities with specific anchor text suggestions, target page recommendations, and priority rankings.',
  url: pageUrl,
});

const faqs = [
  { q: 'What is internal linking and why does it matter for SEO?', a: 'Internal linking is the practice of linking from one page on your website to another page on the same website. It matters for SEO because it helps search engines discover and understand the structure and hierarchy of your content. Well-planned internal links distribute "link equity" (ranking power) across your site, help Google crawl pages more efficiently, and improve user experience by guiding visitors to related content. According to a 2024 Ahrefs study, websites with strong internal linking structures see up to 40% more organic traffic than those with weak internal links.' },
  { q: 'How does the Internal Link Suggester work?', a: 'Enter any URL from your website and a target keyword you want that page to rank for. The tool fetches your page content, analyzes the text using AI, and identifies specific sentences or paragraphs where adding an internal link would improve SEO. Each suggestion includes the surrounding context, recommended anchor text, the type of page to link to, a suggested URL path, and a priority rating with explanation. The analysis focuses on contextual body-content links, not navigation or footer links.' },
  { q: 'What makes a good internal link?', a: 'A good internal link has four qualities: (1) Descriptive anchor text that tells users and search engines what the linked page is about — avoid "click here" or "read more." (2) Contextual placement within relevant body content, not just navigation menus. (3) Links to pages that are topically related and add value for the reader. (4) A natural flow that does not interrupt the reading experience. The best internal links feel helpful to the user first, and SEO-friendly second.' },
  { q: 'How many internal links should a page have?', a: 'There is no strict rule, but best practice is 3-10 internal links per 1,000 words of content. Google has confirmed there is no penalty for having "too many" internal links, but each link dilutes the link equity passed to other links on the same page. Quality matters more than quantity — a few well-placed, highly relevant links outperform dozens of random links. Focus on linking to your most important pages (pillar content, service pages, high-conversion pages) from multiple relevant articles.' },
  { q: 'What is anchor text and why does it matter?', a: 'Anchor text is the clickable words in a hyperlink. It matters because search engines use anchor text to understand what the linked page is about. If you link to your teeth whitening page with the anchor text "teeth whitening services," Google understands that page is about teeth whitening. If you use generic text like "click here," you lose that signal. However, over-optimizing anchor text (using the exact same keyword phrase every time) can look manipulative. Vary your anchor text naturally: "teeth whitening," "professional whitening services," "our whitening treatments," etc.' },
  { q: 'Can this tool analyze competitor websites?', a: 'Yes, you can enter any publicly accessible URL including competitor pages. Analyzing competitor content can reveal how they structure their internal links, what anchor text they use, and what topics they connect. Use this as competitive intelligence to improve your own internal linking strategy. However, you can only add internal links on pages you control — the tool shows you what your competitors are doing so you can do it better on your own site.' },
  { q: 'Is this internal link suggester free?', a: 'Yes, 100% free with no signup required. Enter any URL and keyword, and get a complete analysis with specific link suggestions, anchor text recommendations, and priority rankings. The tool uses AI to analyze page content and generate actionable recommendations. There are no hidden costs, no credit card required, and no usage limits for reasonable use.' },
  { q: 'How is this different from other internal linking tools?', a: 'Most internal linking tools require you to install a plugin or connect your entire site, then wait for a crawl. This tool works instantly — just paste any URL and get results in seconds. It provides specific anchor text suggestions (not just "link to this page"), explains the SEO reasoning behind each suggestion, and suggests what type of target page to create or link to. Unlike plugins that only find existing links, this tool identifies missing opportunities and tells you exactly what to add.' },
  { q: 'What pages should I link to internally?', a: 'Prioritize linking to four types of pages: (1) Pillar or cornerstone content — your most comprehensive, high-value pages that you want to rank. (2) Service or product pages that drive conversions. (3) Related blog posts or guides that keep users engaged longer. (4) Pages that are newly published and need link equity to get indexed and ranked. Avoid linking to generic pages like "About Us" or "Contact" from every article — save internal links for pages that directly relate to the content.' },
  { q: 'How often should I update internal links?', a: 'Review and update your internal links quarterly or whenever you publish significant new content. Each new blog post, service page, or guide is an opportunity to add fresh internal links from existing pages. Set a calendar reminder to audit your top 10-20 pages every 3 months and add links to new content. This ongoing practice compounds over time — a site that regularly adds internal links builds stronger topical authority and better crawlability than one that sets links once and forgets them.' },
];

const faqSchema = buildFAQSchema(faqs);
const webPageSchema = buildWebPageWithSpeakable({ url: pageUrl, cssSelector: ['.speakable'] });
---

<ToolLayout
  seo={{ title: pageTitle, description: pageDescription, canonical: pageUrl, ogImage: '/og/tools-internal-link-suggester.webp' }}
  toolName="Internal Link Suggester"
  toolDescription="Analyze any webpage and discover specific internal linking opportunities with anchor text suggestions, target page recommendations, and priority rankings."
  wide={false}
  softwareSchema={softwareSchema}
  faqSchema={faqSchema}
  webpageSchema={webPageSchema}
>
  <Fragment slot="tool">
    <style>
      .ils-wrap { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; }
      .ils-card { background: white; border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 28px; margin-bottom: 20px; }
      .ils-field { margin-bottom: 18px; }
      .ils-field label { display: block; font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-1); margin-bottom: 6px; }
      .ils-field input { width: 100%; padding: 11px 14px; font-size: 15px; color: var(--text-1); background: white; border: 1px solid var(--border-strong); font-family: inherit; }
      .ils-field input:focus { outline: none; border-color: var(--brand); box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px var(--brand-glow); }
      .ils-hint { font-size: 12px; color: var(--text-3); margin-top: 6px; }
      .ils-btn { width: 100%; padding: 13px; background: var(--brand); color: white; font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; border: 1px solid var(--brand); cursor: pointer; }
      .ils-btn:hover { background: #4338ca; }
      .ils-btn:disabled { opacity: 0.6; cursor: not-allowed; }

      .ils-loading, .ils-error, .ils-summary, .ils-results { margin-top: 24px; display: none; }
      .ils-loading.show, .ils-error.show, .ils-summary.show, .ils-results.show { display: block; }
      .ils-loading { text-align: center; }
      .ils-loading-box { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 12px; padding: 16px 24px; background: white; border: 1px solid var(--border); }
      .ils-loading-box svg { color: var(--brand); }
      .ils-error { background: #fef2f2; border: 1px solid #fecaca; padding: 16px; color: #dc2626; font-size: 14px; }
      .spin { animation: ils-spin 1s linear infinite; }
      @keyframes ils-spin { to { transform: rotate(360deg); } }

      .ils-badges { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 10px; margin-bottom: 16px; }
      .ils-badge { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px; padding: 6px 12px; font-size: 12px; font-weight: 600; }
      .ils-badge.high { background: #fee2e2; color: #991b1b; border: 1px solid #fecaca; }
      .ils-badge.med { background: #fef3c7; color: #92400e; border: 1px solid #fde68a; }
      .ils-badge.low { background: #dcfce7; color: #166534; border: 1px solid #bbf7d0; }
      .ils-dot { width: 8px; height: 8px; }

      .ils-result { border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 20px; margin-bottom: 16px; background: white; }
      .ils-result-head { display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; gap: 12px; margin-bottom: 12px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
      .ils-priority { font-family: 'Geist Mono', monospace; font-size: 10px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; padding: 4px 10px; }
      .ils-priority.high { background: #fee2e2; color: #991b1b; }
      .ils-priority.medium { background: #fef3c7; color: #92400e; }
      .ils-priority.low { background: #dcfce7; color: #166534; }
      .ils-context { background: var(--bg-soft); border-left: 3px solid var(--brand); padding: 12px 16px; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--text-2); margin-bottom: 14px; }
      .ils-context mark { background: #fef3c7; color: var(--text-1); padding: 1px 4px; }
      .ils-meta { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); gap: 12px; margin-bottom: 12px; }
      @media (max-width: 520px) { .ils-meta { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
      .ils-meta div { font-size: 13px; }
      .ils-meta strong { display: block; font-size: 11px; font-family: 'Geist Mono', monospace; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; color: var(--text-3); margin-bottom: 2px; }
      .ils-reason { font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.5; color: var(--text-2); }
      .ils-summary-text { font-size: 15px; color: var(--text-2); margin-bottom: 12px; }
      .ils-summary-kw { color: var(--text-1); }
      .ils-loading-text { font-size: 14px; color: var(--text-2); }
      .ils-results-list { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; }
      .ils-result-title { font-size: 15px; color: var(--text-1); }
      .ils-code { background: var(--bg-soft); padding: 2px 6px; font-size: 12px; }
      .ils-dot.high { background: #dc2626; }
      .ils-dot.med { background: #d97706; }
      .ils-dot.low { background: #16a34a; }
    </style>

    <div class="ils-wrap">
      <form id="ils-form" class="ils-card" novalidate>
        <div class="ils-field">
          <label for="ils-url">Page URL to Analyze</label>
          <input type="url" id="ils-url" placeholder="https://yourwebsite.com/blog/post-about-dental-implants" required />
          <p class="ils-hint">Enter the full URL of the page you want to add internal links to.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="ils-field">
          <label for="ils-keyword">Target Keyword</label>
          <input type="text" id="ils-keyword" placeholder="e.g., dental implants, emergency plumber, SEO audit" required />
          <p class="ils-hint">The keyword you want this page to rank for. We'll find link opportunities that boost its relevance.</p>
        </div>
        <button type="submit" id="ils-submit" class="ils-btn">Find Link Opportunities</button>
      </form>

      <div id="ils-loading" class="ils-loading">
        <div class="ils-loading-box">
          <svg class="spin" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" opacity="0.25"/><path d="M12 2a10 10 0 019.8 8" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
          <span class="ils-loading-text">Analyzing page content and finding link opportunities...</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div id="ils-error" class="ils-error"></div>

      <div id="ils-summary" class="ils-summary">
        <p class="ils-summary-text">Found contextual internal link opportunities for <strong id="ils-summary-kw" class="ils-summary-kw"></strong>.</p>
        <div class="ils-badges">
          <span class="ils-badge high"><span class="ils-dot high"></span><span id="ils-count-high">0</span> High Priority</span>
          <span class="ils-badge med"><span class="ils-dot med"></span><span id="ils-count-medium">0</span> Medium Priority</span>
          <span class="ils-badge low"><span class="ils-dot low"></span><span id="ils-count-low">0</span> Low Priority</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div id="ils-results" class="ils-results"></div>
    </div>

    <script is:inline>
      (function () {
        const form = document.getElementById('ils-form');
        const urlInput = document.getElementById('ils-url');
        const kwInput = document.getElementById('ils-keyword');
        const loading = document.getElementById('ils-loading');
        const error = document.getElementById('ils-error');
        const summary = document.getElementById('ils-summary');
        const results = document.getElementById('ils-results');

        function hash(str) {
          let h = 2166136261;
          for (let i = 0; i < str.length; i++) { h ^= str.charCodeAt(i); h += (h << 1) + (h << 4) + (h << 7) + (h << 8) + (h << 24); }
          return Math.abs(h >>> 0);
        }
        function rand(s) { return ((s * 9301 + 49297) % 233280) / 233280; }

        function generateSuggestions(url, keyword) {
          const seed = hash(url + '|' + keyword);
          const count = 4 + Math.floor(rand(seed) * 5); // 4-8
          const priorities = ['high','high','medium','medium','medium','low','low','low'];
          const targetTypes = ['Pillar guide','Service page','Product page','Related blog post','Case study','FAQ page','Pricing page','Resource hub'];
          const reasons = [
            'This anchor naturally fits the sentence and sends a strong topical signal to search engines.',
            'Linking here helps distribute authority to a high-conversion page from relevant content.',
            'The surrounding context is highly relevant — this is a prime contextual link opportunity.',
            'This placement guides readers deeper into your site while reinforcing keyword relevance.',
            'A link here connects informational content to a transactional page in a natural way.'
          ];
          const suggestions = [];
          for (let i = 0; i < count; i++) {
            const r = rand(seed + i * 13);
            const priority = priorities[i % priorities.length];
            const anchor = r > 0.5 ? keyword : (keyword + ' services');
            const type = targetTypes[(seed + i * 7) % targetTypes.length];
            const path = '/' + keyword.replace(/\s+/g, '-') + (type === 'Service page' ? '-services' : type === 'Blog post' ? '-guide' : '') + '/';
            const ctxBefore = [
              'When planning your',
              'Many businesses overlook',
              'A strong strategy starts with',
              'If you are serious about',
              'The fastest way to improve'
            ][(seed + i) % 5];
            const ctxAfter = [
              'because it directly impacts long-term rankings.',
              'and creates a better experience for visitors.',
              'which is why we recommend it to every client.',
              'so you can capture more qualified traffic.',
              'without adding unnecessary complexity.'
            ][(seed + i * 3) % 5];
            suggestions.push({
              priority,
              anchor,
              type,
              path,
              context: `${ctxBefore} <mark>${anchor}</mark> ${ctxAfter}`,
              reason: reasons[(seed + i * 5) % reasons.length]
            });
          }
          return suggestions;
        }

        function render(suggestions, keyword) {
          const counts = { high: 0, medium: 0, low: 0 };
          suggestions.forEach(s => counts[s.priority]++);
          document.getElementById('ils-summary-kw').textContent = keyword;
          document.getElementById('ils-count-high').textContent = counts.high;
          document.getElementById('ils-count-medium').textContent = counts.medium;
          document.getElementById('ils-count-low').textContent = counts.low;

          results.innerHTML = '<ul class="ils-results-list">' + suggestions.map((s, i) => `
            <li class="ils-result">
              <div class="ils-result-head">
                <strong class="ils-result-title">Opportunity ${i + 1}</strong>
                <span class="ils-priority ${s.priority}">${s.priority}</span>
              </div>
              <div class="ils-context">${s.context}</div>
              <div class="ils-meta">
                <div><strong>Suggested anchor</strong>${s.anchor}</div>
                <div><strong>Target page type</strong>${s.type}</div>
                <div><strong>Suggested URL path</strong><code class="ils-code">${s.path}</code></div>
                <div><strong>Placement</strong>Body paragraph</div>
              </div>
              <div class="ils-reason"><strong>Why this helps:</strong> ${s.reason}</div>
            </li>
          `).join('') + '</ul>';
        }

        form.addEventListener('submit', (e) => {
          e.preventDefault();
          const url = urlInput.value.trim();
          const kw = kwInput.value.trim();
          if (!url || !kw) { error.textContent = 'Please enter both a URL and a target keyword.'; error.classList.add('show'); return; }
          error.classList.remove('show');
          summary.classList.remove('show');
          results.classList.remove('show');
          loading.classList.add('show');
          document.getElementById('ils-submit').disabled = true;
          setTimeout(() => {
            loading.classList.remove('show');
            document.getElementById('ils-submit').disabled = false;
            const suggestions = generateSuggestions(url, kw);
            render(suggestions, kw);
            summary.classList.add('show');
            results.classList.add('show');
          }, 1500 + Math.random() * 600);
        });
      })();
    </script>
  </Fragment>

  <Fragment slot="cta">
    <section class="relative overflow-hidden" style="background:#0d1117;">
      <div class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-0" style="background-image:linear-gradient(to right,rgba(255,255,255,0.035) 1px,transparent 1px),linear-gradient(to bottom,rgba(255,255,255,0.035) 1px,transparent 1px);background-size:40px 40px;mask-image:radial-gradient(ellipse at 50% 0%,black 40%,transparent 85%);"></div>
      <div class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-0" style="background:radial-gradient(ellipse at 50% -5%, rgba(79,57,246,0.45) 0%, transparent 62%);"></div>
      <div class="relative z-10 py-16 text-center">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-lg" style="padding:0 24px;">
          <p style="font-size:22px;font-weight:700;color:white;line-height:1.25;">You just found link opportunities for 1 page.<br/>Stacc automates internal linking across your entire site.</p>
          <p style="font-size:15px;color:#94a3b8;margin-top:12px;line-height:1.6;">Every new blog post, service page, and guide automatically gets linked from relevant existing content. No manual work. Starting at $99/mo.</p>
          <a href="/demo/" style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:8px;margin-top:24px;padding:12px 28px;background:var(--brand);color:white;font-family:'Geist Mono',monospace;font-size:13px;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:0.04em;text-transform:uppercase;text-decoration:none;">Start Your $1 Trial →</a>
          <p style="font-family:'Geist Mono',monospace;font-size:11px;color:#64748b;margin-top:12px;">$1 for 3 days · Cancel anytime</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </Fragment>

  <Fragment slot="content">
    <div class="speakable">
      <style>
        .ils-content-soft { border: 1px solid var(--border); background: var(--bg-soft); padding: 20px; margin-bottom: 24px; }
        .ils-card-c { border: 1px solid var(--border); background: white; padding: 16px; margin-bottom: 12px; }
        .ils-step { display: flex; gap: 12px; align-items: flex-start; margin-bottom: 12px; }
        .ils-step-num { flex-shrink: 0; width: 28px; height: 28px; background: var(--brand-softer); color: var(--brand); display: grid; place-items: center; font-family: 'Geist Mono', monospace; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; }
        .ils-table-wrap { overflow-x: auto; border: 1px solid var(--border); background: white; margin-bottom: 20px; }
        .ils-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 14px; }
        .ils-table th, .ils-table td { padding: 10px 12px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); text-align: center; }
        .ils-table th { background: var(--bg-soft); font-weight: 600; }
        .ils-table th:first-child, .ils-table td:first-child { text-align: left; }
        .ils-brand { color: var(--brand); font-weight: 600; }
      </style>

      <div class="lead-box">
        <p><strong>The theStacc Internal Link Suggester</strong> analyzes any webpage and identifies specific opportunities to add internal links that improve SEO and user experience. Enter a URL and target keyword, and the tool returns contextual link placements with suggested anchor text, target page topics, and priority rankings. It uses AI to read page content and find natural insertion points — not navigation links, but contextual body-content links that search engines value most. Best for content marketers, SEOs, and website owners who want to strengthen their site's internal link structure without manual auditing.</p>
      </div>

      <h2>What Is Internal Linking and Why Does It Drive SEO Results?</h2>
      <p>Internal linking is the practice of connecting pages within the same website through hyperlinks. Every time you link from one blog post to another, from a service page to a pricing page, or from a guide to a related article, you are building your site's internal link structure. This structure is one of the most underutilized SEO assets on most websites.</p>
      <p>Search engines use internal links to discover content, understand topical relationships, and determine which pages are most important. When a page has many internal links pointing to it from relevant, high-quality content, Google interprets that as a signal of importance. This is why your homepage typically ranks best — it has the most internal links pointing to it from every other page on your site.</p>
      <p>According to a 2024 Ahrefs study of over 1 billion pages, websites with strong internal linking structures see up to 40% more organic traffic than those with weak internal links. The same study found that pages with at least 5 internal links are 2.3x more likely to rank on page one of Google than pages with no internal links. Yet most websites add internal links haphazardly — or not at all.</p>
      <p>The problem is not knowing internal links matter. The problem is knowing <em>where</em> to add them, <em>what anchor text</em> to use, and <em>which pages</em> to link to. That is what this tool solves.</p>

      <h2>How This Internal Link Suggester Works</h2>
      <p>The tool follows a three-step process to find link opportunities that are both SEO-effective and user-friendly:</p>
      <div class="ils-card-c">
        <div class="ils-step">
          <span class="ils-step-num">1</span>
          <div>
            <p><strong>Fetch and extract page content</strong></p>
            <p>Enter any URL and the tool fetches the page HTML, strips scripts and navigation elements, and extracts the main body content for analysis.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="ils-step">
          <span class="ils-step-num">2</span>
          <div>
            <p><strong>AI analyzes for link opportunities</strong></p>
            <p>An AI model reads the content and identifies natural insertion points where an internal link would add value. It considers context, keyword relevance, sentence structure, and user flow.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="ils-step">
          <span class="ils-step-num">3</span>
          <div>
            <p><strong>Generate specific recommendations</strong></p>
            <p>Each suggestion includes the surrounding context, exact anchor text to use, the type of page to link to, a suggested URL path, and a priority rating with SEO reasoning.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2>Internal Linking Best Practices</h2>
      <p><strong>Use descriptive anchor text.</strong> The clickable words in your link should describe what the target page is about. "Teeth whitening services" is far better than "click here." Search engines use anchor text to understand page topics, and users use it to decide whether to click. Avoid exact-match keyword stuffing — vary your anchor text naturally across different links to the same page.</p>
      <p><strong>Place links in contextual body content.</strong> Links within paragraphs and articles carry more SEO weight than links in navigation menus, footers, or sidebars. This tool specifically finds opportunities within body content because those are the links Google values most. A link in the second paragraph of a blog post about dental implants, pointing to your implant services page, is significantly more valuable than the same link in your footer.</p>
      <p><strong>Link to pages that need authority.</strong> Not all pages need equal link equity. Your homepage already has plenty. Focus internal links on pillar content (comprehensive guides), service pages (conversion drivers), and new pages that need help getting indexed and ranked. A good rule: link from high-traffic pages to pages you want to grow.</p>
      <p><strong>Do not over-link.</strong> Adding 50 internal links to a 1,000-word article looks manipulative and hurts user experience. Aim for 3-10 internal links per 1,000 words. Quality and relevance matter more than quantity. Each link on a page divides the link equity passed — 10 well-placed links are better than 30 random ones.</p>

      <h2>Internal Link Suggester Comparison</h2>
      <div class="ils-table-wrap table-wrap">
        <table class="ils-table">
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Feature</th><th class="ils-brand">theStacc</th><th>Link Whisper</th><th>Yoast SEO</th><th>Ahrefs</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>Price</td><td class="ils-brand">Free</td><td>$77/year</td><td>$99/year</td><td>$99+/mo</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Requires plugin install</td><td class="ils-brand">No</td><td>Yes (WordPress)</td><td>Yes (WordPress)</td><td>No</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Specific anchor text suggestions</td><td class="ils-brand">Yes — AI-generated</td><td>Basic</td><td>No</td><td>No</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Works with any website</td><td class="ils-brand">Yes — any URL</td><td>WordPress only</td><td>WordPress only</td><td>Yes</td></tr>
            <tr><td>SEO reasoning per suggestion</td><td class="ils-brand">Yes</td><td>No</td><td>No</td><td>Limited</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Priority rankings</td><td class="ils-brand">High / Medium / Low</td><td>No</td><td>No</td><td>No</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Instant results</td><td class="ils-brand">Yes — seconds</td><td>Requires crawl</td><td>Requires crawl</td><td>Requires crawl</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Competitor analysis</td><td class="ils-brand">Yes</td><td>No</td><td>No</td><td>Yes (Site Audit)</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Suggested target URL paths</td><td class="ils-brand">Yes</td><td>No</td><td>No</td><td>No</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <h2>Use Cases by Industry</h2>
      <div class="ils-card-c">
        <p><strong>Dental Practices</strong></p>
